description:
"I'm Out" is a song recorded by American recording artist Ciara, for her eponymously-titled fifth album, featuring guest vocals from American female rapper Nicki Minaj. It was co-written by Rock City, Onika Maraj and Ciara herself and was produced by Rock City and The Co-Captains. The song made its premiere on May 22, 2013 on Ciara's official SoundCloud account and was serviced to Urban contemporary radio in the United States on June 3, 2013 as the second single from Ciara through Epic Records. Lyrically, it incorporates themes of breakups and making an ex-boyfriend regret leaving.
